lipsync-sdk
-----------

This SDK incorporates code, algorithms, and animation-envelope parameters
from the TalkingHead project:

  TalkingHead
  https://github.com/met4citizen/TalkingHead
  Copyright (c) 2023–2026 Mika Suominen ("met4citizen")
  Licensed under the MIT License.

Specifically derived from TalkingHead:

  - modules/lipsync-en.mjs    (English word→viseme conversion)
  - modules/lipsync-fi.mjs    (Finnish word→viseme conversion)
  - modules/lipsync-de.mjs    (German word→viseme conversion)
  - modules/lipsync-fr.mjs    (French word→viseme conversion)
  - modules/lipsync-lt.mjs    (Lithuanian word→viseme conversion)

  Each of these files retains its original @author header. They are
  taken verbatim from the upstream modules/ directory.

  - lipsync-core.mjs  _eventsToFrames envelope timing (ramp-in at
    t − 2d/3, peak at t + d/2, ramp-out at t + d + d/2), and the
    peak-level convention 0.9 for PP/FF and 0.6 otherwise.
    These match the viseme animation queue in TalkingHead's
    talkinghead.mjs streamAudio / _processLipsyncData paths.

Additions unique to lipsync-sdk (not in upstream):

  - Oculus-viseme → ARKit-blendshape weight table
    (lipsync-core.mjs VISEME_BLENDSHAPES). TalkingHead treats
    visemes as morph targets directly (viseme_aa, viseme_PP, ...);
    this SDK maps them to the 52 ARKit blendshapes so the same
    lipsync data can drive ARKit-only avatars.

  - AFAN binary frame format (magic 0x4146414E, version 2,
    fps + numBS + uint32LE numFrames + uint8 blendshape bytes).
    Enables streaming blendshape frames to downstream tools as a
    compact binary without JSON overhead.

  - trackToFrames / estimateWordTimings helpers for building a
    fixed-fps frame array from text + total audio duration when
    per-word TTS timestamps are not available.

